text: So it starts by introducing us to a fun loving water sports enthusiast who ventures out with/without friends to do x water sport, something goes wrong (possibly introduction of shark) and gets separated from friends if present. Stranded on tiny rock, most of the film involves her shouting for help and vainly trying to swim for shore but fear/pain/danger overtakes her each time and she has to return. Shark appears at some point during this struggle to increase tension. Climax begins with the rising tide, eventually forcing her to make frantic swim for shore - this is where lots of close-ups of bloody leg will be, with blood misting into the sea, cut to shark turning swiftly as if in response. snap back and forth from frantic woman and hunting shark. Tussle ensues close to shore which involves shark teeth and a kicking woman, possibly makeshift weapons are produced to fight off shark. Heroic woman makes it to safety. Turns round to find native island dwelling cannibals sharpening knives. End  Well maybe the cannibals are my touch of creative license - but for the most part, I've saved you a cinema ticket.

text: Fucking ridiculous movie. It started out well, I actually really enjoyed it, and then they just over exaggerated it far too much that it just became unrealistic and not enjoyable. They made so many mistakes such as a moment in the film where she is calculating the sharks movements... taking 32 seconds to circle around and come back. As soon as she starts filming, there is not a shark in sight. Secondly, you can see how clear the water is, keep in mind she is still in fairly shallow water too. However, every time she tried to look for the shark, she can't see it, and then suddenly it comes from nowhere. When they film the shark from bird-eye view, it is clearly visible. There's so many more problems, such as how the scar on her leg doesn't fit the size of the shark jaw even slightly, she somehow has phone reception out in the middle of nowhere at a beach. The list just goes on and on. Not worth the watch in my opinion. If you are picky like me, and wanted this movie to portray a realistic scare thriller for you, this is not the one. I must admit, I was clinching my hands at times, and it was tense, but just not realistic and didn't actually scare me. I would rate 4/10.
